			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Recently, everyones favorite president announced a long term plan to re-vitalize the US (and world) space program, to include another manned mission to the moon, and a manned mission to Mars by 2030.  Again, recently we landed a new and improved rover on Mars which has been sending back some (I think) amazing color pictures.  
<br />

<br />
A few days ago at work we were watching the 5:00am news, waiting for the shift to mercifully end, and a story came on about the rover and showed a few of the first color photos of Mars taken from the ground.  Two of my co-workers, both college educated, both thought it was stupid, a waste of money.  I was stunned.  Thus to my point...
<br />

<br />
What are your thoughts on space exploration?  Is it a waste of money?  Should we be spending that money trying to fix problems here on earth?  
<br />

<br />
Personally I am fascinated by space and spacial sciences.  I wish I had a stronger math and physics background since a lot of what I read on the subject ends up being gibberish to me due to lack of understanding on my part...and I'm still fascinated by it.  Science and technology are what have given us the lives we have today and allow for the vast majority of the comforts we enjoy.  To me, ignoring space is a huge mistake.  We are quickly over-populating this rock and sucking up it's resources, we're going to have to get off it sooner or later (or introduce some very stringent birth control policies).  One of my biggest regrets is that I'll only get a century (give or take) of life, and won't get to watch the universe unfold.
<br />

<br />
I'll close with a quote from Carl Segan, scientific badass:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Who are we? We find that we live on an insignificant planet of a humdrum star lost in a galaxy tucked away in some forgotten corner of a universe in which there are far more galaxies than people. - Carl Sagan</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
