				<div class="postbody">
				Personally I think it is a great idea. It has been too long for us to head out from the planet. I figured this was kind of the point of the space station though. 
<br />

<br />
The funding will be a significant problem. But if they are as creative with designs as the first time what new equipment will come out of it? If memory serves the last push is where we got Velcro, Fiber Optics, & Microwave (not exactly sure on last 1). Maybe if the government can hold the patent on any new creations then it would help offset funding. Or allow companys creating it to keep the patents but "donate" their time & services.
<br />

<br />
On the other side what portion of the earth have we left undiscovered so far? Have we sent any significant craft to check out the bottom of the Marianas Trench (sp?)?
<br />

<br />
Even if we do not go out beyond our own solar system I would like to at least see us make it to start mining the asteroid belt. I understand it is ripe with alot of the metals & minerals we use today.
<br />

<br />
Edimas
<br />
Nemesys<br />
