				<div class="postbody">
				If people think that the future of man kind is on earth, they need to think again (imo). There's a lot that is yet to be done, and a lot that needs to be done. Technology is growing faster and faster, but it is about time that technology really started to "spread its wings" and take us farther than ever before. Moore's Law is in full effect, and is about to explode... and it's about time. The rovers on Mars were in development for what, a year? Imagine what could be done with a few years worth of planning and solid development... we've barely scratched the surface of what we're capable of.<br />
