				I liked Red Mars quite a bit, but Green Mars put me off the series.  I know it's sci-fi and all, but the idea just seemed a little silly.  To summarize, humans land on Mars and begin to terraform the planet to a habitable level.  Some environmental zealots fall in love with the planet, and decide it should remain in it's natural state and go around trying to sabatoge the efforts of the terraformers.  I'm not sure what happens in Blue Mars, because I didn't read it.<br />
