			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				There are a number of reasons why the actual terraforming of Mars is not possible. Domed/Underground colonies are certainly within the realm of possibility, but outright terraforming is not.
<br />

<br />
I was watching an episode of Nova about the earth's magnetic field just a few days ago, and it went into great detail about how we are overdue for a pole reversal. Part of this was a discussion of what (probably) happened to Mars. Basically, our magnetic field is what allows us to have an atmosphere. Mars' poles are gone, jump-starting Mars is far far beyond any technology we could feasibly come up with in the next several centuries, most likely.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
